wikipedia_page.main: Charles John Perry Keene (1846 – 29 November 1926) was a British archer who competed at the 1908 Summer Olympics in London. Keene entered the double York round event in 1908, taking tenth place with 543 points. His archery affiliations included the Devon and Cornwall Archery Society of Great Britain.
